Model.Name: tutorial_che_6
Model.Description:
Model of a lithium-ion battery based on porous electrode theory as developed by John Newman and coworkers. In particular, the equations here are based on a summary of the methodology by Karen E. Thomas, John Newman, and Robert M. Darling,
Thomas K., Newman J., Darling R. (2002). Mathematical Modeling of Lithium Batteries in Advances in Lithium-ion Batteries. Springer US. 345-392. `doi:10.1007/0-306-47508-1_13 <http://dx.doi.org/10.1007/0-306-47508-1_13>`_
A few simplifications have been made rather than implementing the more complete model described there. For example, the following assumptions have (currently) been made:
- two porous electrodes are used rather than providing the option for a "half cell" in which one electrode is lithium foil. - conductivity in the electron-conducting phase is infinite - constant exchange current density in Butler-Volmer reaction expression - no electrolyte convection - constant and uniform solvent concentration (ions vary according to concentrated solution theory) - monodisperse particles in electrode - no volume occupied by binder, filler, etc. in the electrode

Object.Name: x_centers_n
Object.Description: X cell-centers domain in negative electrode

Object.Name: x_centers_p
Object.Description: X cell-centers domain in positive electrode

Object.Name: x_centers_full
Object.Description: X cell-centers domain over full cell

Object.Name: x_faces_full
Object.Description: X cell-faces domain over full cell

Object.Name: a_n
Object.Description: Reacting area per electrode volume, negative electrode

Object.Name: a_p
Object.Description: Reacting area per electrode volume, positive electrode

Object.Name: tau_ramp
Object.Description: Time scale for ramping voltage or current

Object.Name: phi1_n
Object.Description: Electric potential in bulk sld, negative

Object.Name: phi1_p
Object.Description: Electric potential in bulk sld, positive

Object.Name: y_avg
Object.Description: Average filling fraction in the solid
